# Provider Conventions

## SDK Source of Truth

All resources and data sources wrap `github.com/zscaler/zscaler-sdk-go/v3`, vendored at
`vendor/github.com/zscaler/zscaler-sdk-go/v3/zscaler/zia/services/`. Fields and CRUD
functions must exist in the SDK before being added to the provider.

## Resource Pattern

Every resource has three structs in a single file:

```go
type FooArgs struct {
    Name *string `pulumi:"name,optional"`
}

type FooState struct {
    FooArgs
    ResourceId string `pulumi:"resourceId"`
}

type Foo struct{}
```

## Annotate Methods

- Resource-level: **value receiver**, use `describeResource(a, &Foo{}, "...")` helper
- Args/State-level: **pointer receiver**, use `a.Describe(&a.Field, "...")`
- Functions: **pointer receiver** on all three (function, args, result)

## Documentation in Annotate

Include Hugo shortcodes for Pulumi Registry rendering:

```go
describeResource(a, &Foo{}, "Description.\n\n"+
    "{{% examples %}}\n## Example Usage\n\n{{% example %}}\n"+
    tripleBacktick("typescript")+"\n// code\n"+tripleBacktick("")+"\n"+
    "{{% /example %}}\n{{% /examples %}}")
```

## Registration

- Resources: `infer.Resource(Foo{})` in `provider.go` `WithResources()`
- Functions: `infer.Function(&GetFoo{})` in `provider.go` `WithFunctions()`

## Client Access

```go
cfg := infer.GetConfig[Config](ctx)
svc := cfg.Client().Service
```

## Activation

Call `triggerActivation(ctx, cfg.Client())` after CRUD if `shouldActivate()` returns true.
